      <body>Good catch -- it definitely slipped my mind.

I would only change the check like this:

@@@ ruby
if left =~ /&lt;[^&gt;]+$/ &amp;&amp; right =~ /^[^&lt;]+&gt;/
@@@

Now the right regexp reflects the left.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Good catch -- it definitely slipped my mind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I would only change the check like this:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
if left =~ /&amp;lt;[^&amp;gt;]+$/ &amp;amp;&amp;amp; right =~ /^[^&amp;lt;]+&amp;gt;/
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now the right regexp reflects the left.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
